reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Pretty design and great for keyboard and mouse.
reviews.reviewText: Not too padded, so don't buy this for wrist comfort or anything, but that's not what I bought it for anyway. Serves as a nice mouse pad and looks great on my desk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Wasn't used to the material but my mouse glides along it well
reviews.reviewText: I've only ever had fabric mouse pads. Before this one, I had 2 other mousepads that eventually fell victim to my aggressive mouse movements and threads started coming apart making it difficult to move my mouse smoothly. I ordered this thinking that it's a fabric mousepad, but when I took it out of the box, it was leather. It had a hard time laying out flat after unrolling it from its tightly coiled form which was my one complaint, but it eventually flattened out.It's pretty good when comparing it to my $40 and $30 mousepads. For $18, it does the same thing but maybe not as pretty. It's made moving my mouse a lot easier though! No more loose threads to worry about. I can tell that I'll be able to use this for a long time. I've also used this to hold my coffee or water and I've spilt some coffee on it, and it was easy to clean off.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not what I was expecting.
reviews.reviewText: When I received the Laokiiy Desk Mat, it was tightly rolled in its packaging and wasn't willing to flatten out. even days after unboxing. The mat itself has several creases running through it that I can't get rid of and find to be a distraction on the desk. Please refer to the photos.The material is good quality and the mat is an ok cover for the desk surface if you plan to place items on it. However, being that it's slightly foamlike, it's does not the best surface to write on.The Laokiiy Desk Mat is "ok" if you just want something low cost and plan to put a bunch of stuff on but it's not a great looking piece if you have OCD or care at all about a pristine appearance since the creases may never go away. Perhaps ironing it might help? That's too much work for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not very anti-slip, but still great
reviews.reviewText: I got this desk mat to brighten up my desk and to protect the wood from coffee or water spills. The size was absolutely perfect for the space that I intended it for. I love the colors and they are just as vibrant as pictured in the product listing. The mat arrived rolled up, and it took a while with weighted items holding it down to get the mat to remain unrolled at the ends. Although the listing states that this mat is anti-slip, I did not find it to be very effective at that. It is, however, extremely easy to clean and is great at protecting my desk. If you need an anti-slip mat, this probably would not be a good choice. But if you want a mat that looks great, is easy to clean, and protects your desk, this is a great option.
